definitions.definition: The prehistoric period intermediate between the earliest period (‘ Paleo-Indian ’, ‘Paleo-American’, ‘American‐paleolithic’, etc.) of human presence in the Western Hemisphere , and the most recent prehistoric period (‘Woodland’, etc.).
an archaic variety of Homo sapiens .

main_definition: ( archaeology , US , usually capitalized ) The prehistoric period intermediate between the earliest period (‘ Paleo-Indian ’, ‘Paleo-American’, ‘American‐paleolithic’, etc.) of human presence in the Western Hemisphere , and the most recent prehistoric period (‘Woodland’, etc.).
secondary_definitions: ( paleoanthropology ) (A member of) an archaic variety of Homo sapiens .
